<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>Re: DOT Spells Illegal In PvP?????</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois2.cgi?Phazer">Phazer</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 2:23 a.m. 25/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> Re: DOT Spells Illegal In PvP?????<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/pvpquest/images/divider.gif" width=452 height=22 border=0></center><BR><P ALIGN=CENTER><b>In Reply To:</b> <A HREF="http://www.everworld.net/cgi-local/pvp.cgi?read=1942" TARGET=_self>DOT Spells Illegal In PvP?????</A> (Yvanos, Priest of Innoruuk)
</STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#FFFFFF FACE=arial>
<P>> Today, on the EQVault PvP board, Bran of CC claimed a /broadcast

<BR>&gt; last night stated that casting DOT spells on another player --
<BR>&gt; ANY
<BR>&gt; player -- was an exploit & cause for suspension &/or
<BR>&gt; banning.
<P>&gt; I never saw this message, but I logged out at 7:00 PST. My
<BR>&gt; nephew
<BR>&gt; didn't log in until after South Park ended (10:30 PST) & he
<BR>&gt; never
<BR>&gt; saw the message either.
<P>&gt; Was this a joke, or was it actually broadcast? Personally, I
<BR>&gt; think
<BR>&gt; he's full of fecal matter, but hey... I could be wrong.
<P>It is true, the reason of this is because when you use DOT spells against another player in combat they lose experiance. I would think this would be a simple patch fix, but obvisouly its much deeper than that. I hope someday they can go around this, but it is pretty lame because most Necromancers depend on DOT spells to kill other players. Same rule applies with the invising another player to make their pet dissapear.
<P>----------------------
<BR>Phazer AKA Phazling
<BR>phazer@evatac.com
<BR>----------------------
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
